Date: 0/0/1888
Source: Birds of New Zealand
Author: BULLER
Vol / Page: 1/42
Edition:
Quote: MYIOMOIRA MACROCEPHALA. (SOUTH-ISLAND TOMTIT.) <i>Native names</i>. Miromiro, Komiromiro, Pimiromiro, Ngirungiru, Pingirungiru, and Pipitori. ... Its note in the early morning is like the Maori syllables <i>ngi-i-ru, ngiru-ngiru</i>, from which it derives its name, the first syllable being rather prolonged.
